IBM's loss of Apple as a customer is not a major blow, as Intel gains a high-profile win.
Apple's switch to Intel chips is seen as a move to compete with Microsoft and Sony.
The transition is expected to allow Apple to lower prices and focus on powerful processors for gaming consoles.
Despite concerns, Apple's reputation for design and software is expected to remain strong.
The move signifies a shift in the industry towards consumer electronics.
